data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的单数名词

data.enText: the group of people who are elected to make and change the laws of a country
The German parliament is called the ‘Bundestag’.

data.chText: 英国议会（包括下议院和上议院）

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的不可数名词

data.enText: the parliament of the United Kingdom, consisting of the House of Commons and the House of Lords

data.chText: 议会就这个问题进行了辩论。
data.enText: the issue was debated in Parliament

data.chText: 赢得议会中的一个席位
data.enText: to win a seat in Parliament

data.chText: 一届议会的会期；（两次大选之间的）一届议会
data.enText: a particular period during which a parliament is working; Parliament as it exists between one general election and the next

data.chText: 我们现已进入了本届议会的后半任期。
data.enText: We are now into the second half of the parliament.

data.chText: 解散议会并下令举行大选
data.enText: to dissolve Parliament (= formally end its activities) and call an election

simple_means.memory_skill: parl 说，谈 + ia + ment 组织，机构 → 大家讨论国家大事 → 国会

means: 英国议会(包括下议院和上议院)

ex.chText: 你所说的“议会自由”是什么意思？
ex.enText: What do you mean by 'a free parliament'?

ex.chText: 该法案议会何时通过的？
ex.enText: When was the bill passed by the Parliament?

synonyms.bx: 指经选举制定法律或商议国事的一群人；首字母大写时，指由上议院和下议院组成的英国国会。

ex.chText: 总统必须赢得国会的支持。
ex.enText: The president has to win the support of Congress.

ex.chText: 国会未对该提案进行投票表决。
ex.enText: Congress didn't vote on that proposal.

synonyms.bx: 与 parliament 基本同义；首字母大写时，指由参议院和众议院组成的美国国会。

tr: a card game in which you play your sevens and other cards in sequence in the same suit as the sevens
you win if you are the first to use all your cards
a legislative assembly in certain countries

value.def: The parliament of some countries, for example Britain, is the group of people who make or change its laws, and decide what policies the country should follow.

example.ex: Parliament today approved the policy, but it has not yet become law.
example.tran: 议会于今天批准了这项政策，但尚未成为法律。

value.def: A particular parliament is a particular period of time in which a parliament is doing its work, between two elections or between two periods of holiday.

example.ex: The legislation is expected to be passed in the next parliament.
example.tran: 预计这项法案将在下一届议会中通过。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to speak, to talk 说, 谈
rootsaffixes.title: parl

partsOfSpeech.dec: parl 说，谈 + ance 表状态 → 说法，用语
parl 说，谈 + ey → 谈判
parl 说，谈 + ia + ment 组织，机构 → 大家讨论国家大事 → 国会
parl 说，谈 + or 表器物 → 客厅，会客室
